   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=993.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Our Response</span><hr size=1> I wasn't there, and my only major concern on this issue was addressed in the very last post.  I wanted to see some response from Awakened Souls.  Not necessarily so I could judge one side against the other, but so I could at least know for sure that Awakened Souls has some regard for their reputation and intends to be a part of the community.<br>
<br>
I have to say, I've had some negative feelings towards Awakened Souls also.  I can't even quote a specific run-in, just very small faction hits along the road that have added up, along with comments by friends and people whose opinions I respect.  A few people I've had good experiences with in the past ended up in AS and I don't imagine they turned to the dark side just because they are wearing a new guild tag, but I still don't have good feelings about the guild as a whole.<br>
<br>
Strangely, this thread now qualifies as the first really good thing I've seen from AS.  Points:  They did play by the rules, even if a good friend of mine lost out I'll acknowledge that.  They are open to other systems, and state that as well, and it's hard to blame them by just doing their best under the system as it exists.  They responded intelligently and maturely, and more than that they all held their tongues until their guild leader himself made an official reply.  By any standard, that's class.  And their stated policy of holding back major quests until the last bottleneck is a reasonable one, in my opinion.<br>
<br>
To Xarpolis, and to Awakened Souls in general, I wish to state as an active member of the community that I at least don't hold this one against you.  But I'd also like to point out that the sum of this situation is not only in the details.  People are willing to believe the worst of your guild right now, and make assumptions against your favour, because of other poor experiences in the past.  If you wish to be a respected part of the high-end community on FV, as Resolution and F&amp;F have managed to be (kudos for agreeing to MA Gore) I hope you are willing to address the small issues as well as the large, and clean up the acts of some of your less reputable members.  Sometimes simply because someone is Uber they still aren't something you want in an &quot;uber&quot; guild.<br>
<br>
Valquiss Silverpalm<br>
